==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[con-]]'' + ''[[fluere]]''

===Noun===
# The point where two [[river]]s or [[stream]]s meet and become one, usually when a [[tributary]] joins a more major river.
# The merger or meeting of two or more objects (or subjects) that seem to inseparably bind their respective forces or attributes into a point of junction.
# A [[convergence]] of peoples.

====Translations====
* Estonian: [[liitumiskoht]]
* French: confluent (masculine noun)

